List folders and files:
	ls <dir> <parameter>

	examples:
	ls -a (list all files, even hidden ones)
	ls -h (list in human format)

Change Directory:
	cd <dir>
	
	examples
	cd .. (go back)
	cd ~ (go to beginning)

Create New Dir(ectory):
	mkdir <name>

Delete Dir(ectory):
	rmdir <name>

Move file / Change Name:
	mv <path/name> <path/name>
	
	tip. you can use to change files name
	mv /home/user/test.txt /home/user/newname.txt
	
Create a txt:
	touch <name>
	
Delete file:
	rm <name>

Copy file:
        cp <path/name> <path/name>
	    (source)	 (dest)

	-f: Force the copy procedure by removing the destination file if needed.

    	-i: Will give you a warning message before overwritting file.

	-u: Will only copy if the source file is newer than destination file.

    	-n: Wonâ€™t copy if the file already exists (Does not overwrite).

	-a: This option will archive the files.	
	
Clear Terminal Screen:
	clear
	or
	Ctrl+L

Open New Terminal Session:
	Ctrl+Alt+T

End Session:
	exit
	or
	Ctrl+D

Copy something in Terminal:
	Ctrl+Shift+C

Paste in Terminal
	Ctrl+Shift+V

Show History
	history
	*history -c (clear history)

Show contests of a file
	cat <file>

Download file from the internet
	wget <url>

Show full path
	pwd 


